    		<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Privacy policy</strong></p>
<p>We treat your privacy in strict accordance with the legislation of the Republic of Uzbekistan. This policy describes what types of information we may collect and store, how that information is used, how we keep it secure, and how you can contact us. We respect your right and confidentiality when filling out, transferring and storing confidential data.</p>
<p>This site registered to SOS Children's Villages of Uzbekistan Association (hereinafter referred to as the Association), located at: 79, Nukus str.,Tashkent, 100015. By using the site https://sos-kd.uz, you agree to the terms of this Policy. We post any changes we make to the Privacy policy on this page. If you do not agree to the terms of this Policy, you should stop using the site.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Information that we collect</strong></p>
<p>Information that you provide yourself while subscribing to regular donations, as well as in the process of further using the site sos-kd.uz, including personal data.</p>
<p>Information about the call, including your name, the reason for contacting us, and the response we give you when you contact us.</p>
<p>We may ask for your contact information, name, interests and preferences while you attend our social events.</p>
<p>We may collect information related to your social network accounts when you visit our social network pages.</p>
<p>Data that is transmitted automatically depending on the settings of the software you use, including IP address, cookies, data about the equipment used, browser parameters and settings, operating system, URL from which the transition was made, page views, time access and your location. This information is tied to the device you use to access the sos-kd.uz website.</p>
<p>The Association does not verify the accuracy of the personal information you provide, believing that you are acting in good faith, prudently and making all necessary efforts to keep such information up to date. You can change (update, supplement) the personal information provided by you or part of it at any time.</p>
<p>For security reasons and in order to comply with the law, the Association stores for a certain period of time data about your messages and requests (including the content of the messages, the time and date of writing the messages), as well as log files about the actions performed by you within the framework of using the site.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Processing of personal data</strong></p>
<p>Personal data means information recorded on electronic, paper and (or) other tangible media, related to a specific individual or making it possible to identify him in accordance with the Law of the Republic of Uzbekistan dated 02.07.2019 #547 &ldquo;On Personal Data&rdquo;.</p>
<p>Processing of personal data - the implementation of one or a combination of actions to collect, systematize, store, change, supplement, use, provide, distribute, transfer, depersonalize and destroy personal data/</p>
<p>We may use the information we collect for a variety of purposes, including:</p>
<p>Providing a personalized service;</p>
<p>Granting access to you to the services that you express willing to use;</p>
<p>Communication with you, including sending notifications, requests and information regarding the use of the site, processing your requests and applications, sending email messages related to the activities of our organization;</p>
<p>Creating anonymous aggregated statistics about the use of our websites, social networks, which we may share with third parties and/or make publicly available;</p>
<p>Improving the quality of the site and customer service.</p>
<p>We may link or combine information obtained from various sources listed above in the "Information We Collect" section.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Ensuring the security of personal data</strong></p>
<p>We do our best to protect your personal information from unauthorized attempts to access, modify, disclose or destroy.</p>
<p>To ensure this, we:</p>
<p>store your personal information on secure servers and prevent unauthorized access to systems that store personal information;</p>
<p>continually improve the way we collect, store and process data, including physical security measures to prevent unauthorized access to our systems;</p>
<p>limit our employees, contractors and agents access to personal data when such access is not required for the purposes specified in this Policy, as well as impose strict contractual obligations on them, for the violation of which liability is provided.</p>
<p>The Association takes the necessary and sufficient technical, organizational and administrative measures to ensure the security of the collected data to protect it from unauthorized access, destruction, modification, blocking, copying, distribution, as well as from other illegal actions of third parties. Web pages containing personal information about the user are protected by Secure Sockets Layer (SSL), a security protocol that ensures secure communications over the Internet.</p>
<p>Access to the collected information can be provided exclusively to employees of the Association who need it to perform their job duties. Exceptions are cases in which the Association is obliged to provide the collected information at the official request of authorized persons in accordance with the legislation of the Republic of Uzbekistan.</p>
<p>By using our website and social networks, you agree to the described conditions.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Cookies</strong></p>
<p>While browsing any page of the site sos-kd.uz, the page itself is downloaded to your computer, as well as a small text file called a cookie. The information we receive through cookies helps us provide services in the most convenient way for you. A cookie is a small amount of data, often including a unique, anonymous identifier, sent to your browser by a website's computer and stored on your computer's hard drive. Visiting the site via web browser that accepts data from cookies means that you agree that the Association may collect and process data from cookies for the purposes provided in this Policy, as well as to transfer data from cookies to third parties in the cases listed in this Policy. Disabling or blocking your web browser's option to accept data from cookies means a prohibition on the collection and processing of data from cookies in accordance with the terms of this Privacy policy.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Access to your information and your rights</strong></p>
<p>If you would like a copy of your personal information that we store in our databases, please contact us using the information in the &ldquo;Contact us&rdquo; section below. You may be asked to provide proof of identification so that we can verify that you are the one making the request.</p>
<p>This is in addition to your legal rights, including the access right to a copy of your personal information, the right to request deletion or updating of inaccurate personal data, and the right to withdraw consent to the processing of your data. You can make use of these rights by contacting us using the information in the &ldquo;Contact us&rdquo; section below.</p>
